        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 6:23PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 623 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hanover, or 8 miles northwest of Welch, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Welch, Pineville, Oceana, Hanover, Davy, Iaeger, Kimball, Clear Fork,
Avondale, Wolf Pen, and Baileysville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
